// Plan A — Research Roadmap (v3, TIER-STRUCTURED, FACT-CHECKED)
//
// Every direction has at least: ★ Flagship (Nature / Nat Methods / Nat Biotechnol)
//                              + ★★ Sub-journal (Nat Commun / eLife)
//                              + ★★★ Baseline (Bioinformatics / Cell Reports Methods)
//
// Fact-checked references (Oct 2024 – May 2026, verified via WebSearch 2026-05-13):
//   - ModelAngelo (Jamali et al., Nature 2024): final training = 3,715 map-model pairs
//     (700 was only the manual-curation first iteration)
//   - Cryo-IEF (Nat Methods 2025): 65M particles, 2D-only
//   - DeepQs: 496 paired training samples
//   - DeepEMhancer (Comm Biol 2021): N2N-style, no clean GT
//   - DiffModeler (PMC 2024): DDIM, intermediate resolution
//   - Foldseek (Nat Biotechnol 2024) + Foldseek-Multimer (Nat Methods 2025): atomic only
//   - AlphaFold-Multimer: 60% dimer success rate
//
// IMPORTANT: ChimeraX molmap produces synthetic clean TARGETS that LACK CTF, missing-wedge,
// and anisotropy of real cryo-EM. We treat these as supervised reference signals, not as
// "perfect ground truth".

